{"id":"41d83318-bbb4-4130-8814-1c8e9b4758bd","companyId":"13e61789-5895-451b-95a8-a7457a310c9e","projectId":"90d1b267-8b11-4b20-abed-2422cd4089fb","projectWorkspaceId":"047a7078-fce3-46a4-aa5e-d66abc0a3f51","goalId":"9db92b35-5e38-432a-ad36-f4cc199f644d","parentId":null,"title":"Post-migration localization sweep — DOM + OCR scan for hardcoded English","description":"## Goal\nWalk the running localized app surface (post-ZAI-75 migration) and produce a structured \"hardcoded-English\" report that the Localizer can act on.\n\nDriver: board directive on [ZAI-67](/ZAI/issues/ZAI-67) at 2026-05-06 14:52:49Z — \"когда миграция будет завершена, пусть QA пройдётся по всему, куда может дотянуться, чтобы собрать данные для Локализатора где ещё что-то на английском захардкожено\".\n\n## Approach (creative DOM + screenshot analysis)\nReuse the ZAI-76 coverage tooling (`qa-coverage-matrix`) and extend it with an English-leak detector:\n\n1. **DOM pass** — visit the same 37+ routes from ZAI-76, switch language to a non-English locale (e.g. `ru` and `de`), then scrape rendered text.\n2. **OCR pass** — capture screenshots, run OCR; cross-check OCR output against DOM text and against the i18n bundles for the active locale.\n3. **English-leak heuristics** — any string that:\n   - appears unchanged across the en→ru toggle, AND\n   - is not a brand/product name, version, code, or date,\n   - flag as \"likely hardcoded English\".\n4. **Per-finding payload** — `{route, selector_or_bbox, sample_text, locale_under_test, severity, suggested_i18n_key}`.\n\n## Deliverables\n- `qa-hardcoded-english-report` issue document (markdown summary + counts per route).\n- JSON attachment with all findings (rows = leaks).\n- Top-N \"biggest offenders\" table (by surface area / route count).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n1. Sweep covers ≥30 routes (parity with ZAI-76 baseline).\n2. Both `ru` and `de` locales tested.\n3. Report distinguishes \"definitely English\" from \"likely English\" via the heuristic, with sample bbox or DOM selector for each finding.\n4. Per-finding suggested i18n key (best-effort namespace + slug) so Localizer can act without re-discovering structure.\n5. Workspace clean at end (no uncommitted noise in the running tree).\n\n## Out of scope\n- Actually translating the leaks — that's a follow-up Localizer task.\n- Adding new i18n keys — Localizer's job, this issue is detection-only.\n\n## Notes\n- Migration deliverable [ZAI-75](/ZAI/issues/ZAI-75) is `done` (10 stages, branch `vib-1171-2652-2760-3582-localization`). [ZAI-13](/ZAI/issues/ZAI-13) is the in-flight merge to master; sweep can run against the branch tree even before merge if you want the data sooner — but flag any findings that may be merge-resolved.\n- Reuse the qa-coverage-matrix tooling rather than rebuilding.\n","status":"in_review","priority":"medium","assigneeAgentId":"db69a3af-4281-40f9-9612-00d9c9c80315","assigneeUserId":null,"checkoutRunId":null,"executionRunId":"03844638-4dfa-442b-90bd-e1897c574360","executionAgentNameKey":"ceo","executionLockedAt":"2026-05-06T21:20:14.064Z","createdByAgentId":"db69a3af-4281-40f9-9612-00d9c9c80315","createdByUserId":null,"issueNumber":79,"identifier":"ZAI-79","originKind":"manual","originId":null,"originRunId":null,"originFingerprint":"default","requestDepth":0,"billingCode":null,"assigneeAdapterOverrides":null,"executionPolicy":{"mode":"normal","stages":[{"id":"50614ca7-c3a1-48c2-82f4-8a248fcf0446","type":"review","participants":[{"id":"010b414b-4cf3-4152-a581-5eac662f7867","type":"agent","userId":null,"agentId":"a6ec4085-a4e5-489c-bd10-7c46f8b62e07"}],"approvalsNeeded":1},{"id":"3fb73cfb-a71d-474b-8b76-504a9e515d22","type":"approval","participants":[{"id":"ad86ac5e-e188-4e23-af69-d96c224718c7","type":"agent","userId":null,"agentId":"db69a3af-4281-40f9-9612-00d9c9c80315"}],"approvalsNeeded":1}],"commentRequired":true},"executionState":{"status":"pending","reviewRequest":null,"currentStageId":"3fb73cfb-a71d-474b-8b76-504a9e515d22","lastDecisionI